---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { icon } from "../lib/icons";

const ext = icon("open", 13);
---

<Layout page="page" title="How it works">
    <div class="content-page">
        <section class="content-section content-intro">
            <div class="container-narrow">
                <p class="eyebrow content-eyebrow">About</p>
                <h1>How it works</h1>
                <p class="content-lede">
                    Manufacturer specs say what a device <em>should</em> do. The Device Database tracks what it
                    <em>actually</em> does, built from anonymized real-world data shared by the community.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-num">1</div>
                        <h3>Community shares anonymized data</h3>
                        <p>
                            Home Assistant users opt in to share what devices they run and how those devices
                            behave. No personal data, no identifiers, no addresses.
                            <a
                                class="content-link"
                                href="https://my.home-assistant.io/redirect/analytics/"
                                target="_blank"
                                rel="noopener">Opt in today.<span set:html={ext} /></a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-num">2</div>
                        <h3>The database aggregates and verifies</h3>
                        <p>
                            Submissions are validated, then aggregated. A device only appears once enough
                            independent contributions have been received.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-num">3</div>
                        <h3>Anyone can look it up, no account needed</h3>
                        <p>
                            You don't have to use Home Assistant to benefit. The Device Database is free, open, and
                            built to help you make more informed decisions.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="container-narrow">
                <h2>What's in an entry</h2>
                <p class="content-prose">
                    Each device page aims to answer the questions that matter most when choosing a device,
                    including compatibility, whether it requires an internet connection, which Home Assistant
                    integration controls it, and what others have actually experienced running it, good or bad.
                </p>
                <p class="content-prose">
                    Where a claim is unverified, the entry says so explicitly. Where the device works one way on
                    one firmware and a different way on another, both are noted. The goal is editorial neutrality
                    and source-backed precision, not marketing copy.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="container-narrow">
                <h2>How to contribute</h2>
                <p class="content-prose">
                    For now, the best way to contribute is to
                    <a
                        class="content-link"
                        href="https://my.home-assistant.io/redirect/analytics/"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener">opt in to Device Analytics in Home Assistant<span set:html={ext} /></a>. Every
                    submission helps grow the database and improve the data available to everyone.
                </p>
                <p class="content-prose">
                    Direct contributions to device pages, such as adding context, correcting details, or sharing
                    first-hand experience, are on our
                    <a
                        class="content-link"
                        href="https://github.com/orgs/OpenHomeFoundation/projects/8/views/1"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener">roadmap<span set:html={ext} /></a>. We're starting light: the immediate focus
                    is making the device data collected so far accessible and useful to everyone through the
                    Preview edition of this website.
                </p>
                <p class="content-prose">
                    <a
                        class="content-link"
                        href="https://github.com/orgs/OHF-Device-Database/discussions"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener">Join the community discussion<span set:html={ext} /></a> and help shape the
                    future of the Device Database.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</Layout>
